1. e4 e6 2. d4 d5 3. Nd2 Nc6 4. Ngf3 Nf6 5. e5 Nd7 6. Bd3 Be7 (6... f6 7. Ng5 Ndxe5 (7... fxg5 8. Qh5+ g6 9. Bxg6+ hxg6 10. Qxg6+ Ke7 11. Ne4 Bh6 12. Bxg5+ Bxg5 13. Qg7+ Ke8 14. Nxg5 Qe7 15. Qg6+ Kd8 16. Nxe6+ Qxe6 17. Qxe6 $16) 8. dxe5 fxg5 9. Qh5+ g6 10. Bxg6+ Kd7 11. c4 Nxe5 12. Bc2 Qf6 $16) 7. O-O b6 { strategic bishop exchange principle instead of castling } (7... O-O 8. c3 b6 9. Qe2 Ncb8 10. Ne4 Ba6 (10... dxe4 11. Qxe4 f5 12. Qxa8 $16) 11. Bxa6 Nxa6 12. Neg5 h6 13. Nxf7 Rxf7 14. Qxa6 $16) 8. Re1 a5 9. c3 Ncb8 { [%cal Bc6b8] } 10. Nf1 Ba6 11. Bc2 c5 12. Ng3 h5 13. dxc5 bxc5 14. Ne2 Nb6 15. Qd2 Rg8 16. Qf4 g5 17. Qg3 Kd7 { connecting rooks principle..also King safety principle } { [%cal Ge8d7] } 18. Nd2 Nc6 19. b3 Qc7 20. f4 gxf4 { possible because rooks are connected - protecting each other } 21. Qxf4 Rg4 22. Qxf7 Nxe5 23. Qh7 Rag8 24. Nf4 (24. g3 Qb8 { Rh8 threat } 25. Qh6 Bg5 26. Qh7+ Kc6 27. Qxh5 Rh8 $17 28. Bh7 Bd3 29. Ne4 Bxe4 30. Nd4+ cxd4 31. Rxe4 Rxe4 32. Bxg5 Qf8 33. Rf1 Qg7 $17) 24... R8g5 { Rxf4 threat } 25. Rxe5 Qxe5 26. Nf3 Qxc3 27. Qf7 (27. Nxg5 Qe1#) 27... Qxf3 28. Qxe6+ Ke8 { end of game } 29. Qc6+ Nd7 30. Bd2 Rxg2+ 31. Kh1 Rg1# { 0-1 Black wins. } 0-1


