[ChapterURL "https://lichess.org/study/vENPCM25/Q6rgMdfD"]
[Annotator "https://lichess.org/@/Kingscrusher-YouTube"]

1. e4 c5 2. Nf3 d6 3. d4 cxd4 4. Nxd4 Nf6 5. f3 { This leaves the option of playing c4 - for the Maroczy bind } 5... e5 { Black weakens the d5 square } (5... d5 6. e5 Ng8 7. f4 $14) 6. Nb3 Be7 7. c4 { The Maroczy bind - a way of prevening d5 from black and also hemming in the e7 dark squared bishop. } 7... a5 8. Be3 a4 9. Nc1 O-O 10. Nc3 Qa5 11. Qd2 Na6 { Black prepares to use the c5 square for the knight } 12. Be2 Nc5 13. O-O Bd7 14. Rb1 Rfc8 15. b4 axb3 16. axb3 { b4 is now threatened } 16... Qd8 17. Nd3 Ne6 18. Nb4 { The d5 square is really good for White here } 18... Bc6 19. Rfd1 { [%cal Gh7h3,Ge2f1,Gd2f2,Gf2b6] } 19... h5 (19... Kh8 20. Ncd5 { [%cal Gd5b6] } 20... Kg8 21. Nb6) 20. Bf1 { [%csl Gh4][%cal Gh5h4,Ge2f1,Gd2f2,Gf2h4] } 20... h4 21. Qf2 Nd7 22. g3 Ra3 23. Bh3 Rca8 24. Nc2 R3a6 25. Nb4 Ra5 26. Nc2 b6 27. Rd2 Qc7 28. Rbd1 Bf8 29. gxh4 Nf4 30. Bxf4 exf4 { Black threatens Ne5 here } 31. Bxd7 Qxd7 (31... Bxd7 32. Nd5 Qd8 33. Nxb6 Rb8 34. b4 Rh5 35. Rd5 $16 Rxd5 36. Nxd5 $16) 32. Nb4 (32. Qxb6 Bb7 33. Qf2 $16) 32... Ra3 33. Nxc6 Qxc6 34. Nb5 Rxb3 (34... Ra1 35. Kh1 R8a2 36. Qe1 Qa8 37. Rxa1 Rxa1 38. Rd1 Ra2 39. Nc3 Rb2 40. Rb1 Rc2 41. Ra1 Qc8 42. Ra2 Rxa2 43. Nxa2 Qh3 44. Qf2 $14) 35. Nd4 Qxc4 36. Nxb3 Qxb3 37. Qe2 Be7 38. Kg2 Qe6 39. h5 Ra3 40. Rd3 Ra2 41. R3d2 Ra3 42. Rd3 Ra7 43. Rd5 Rc7 44. Qd2 Qf6 45. Rf5 Qh4 46. Rc1 Ra7 47. Qxf4 Ra2+ 48. Kh1 Qf2 49. Rc8+ Kh7 50. Qh6+ { 1-0 - black resigned here } 50... Kxh6 (50... gxh6 51. Rxf7#) 51. Rh8# 1-0


