{ I hope this is just one of hundreds of Leela chess studies which the community creates to help generate interest in the fascinating Open Source Neural Network project of Leela Chess. I think this is a new world of mega-exciting games! Some info about Leela Chess:

https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Leela_(software)

Play Leela Chess: http://play.lczero.org/

Leela Chess Forum: https://groups.google.com/forum/#!forum/lczero

Leela Chess Blog: https://blog.lczero.org/

There is something very pleasing deep down to be part of open source projects, in some way, shape or form.

This particular study helps centralise some of Leela's more amazing and outrageous chess games from my personal "Kingscrusher perspective"- and I may try and video annotate contributor games if I think they are super-cool :).

If you wish to contribute game chapters, please let me know - please include Leela ID number and time control. }
