1. e4 c5 2. d4 cxd4 3. c3 d3 4. Bxd3 d6 5. Nf3 { no rush for c4 } 5... Nd7 6. Nbd2 e6 { somehow opponent thinks it is a good idea here - but now c4 is back
potentially } { [%cal Ye7e6,Bg8f6,Bf8e7] } 7. Qe2 Be7 8. c4 Qc7 9. b3 a6 10. Bb2 Bf6 { weakens d6 a bit which
is a fixed target } { [%csl Bd6][%cal Yd1d6,Bg3d6,Ba3d6] } 11. Bxf6 Ngxf6 12. O-O O-O 13. Rfe1 Rd8 14. Rad1 Ne5 15. Bb1 Bd7 16. Nd4 Bc6 17. N2f3 Nxf3+ 18. Qxf3 Rac8 19. Rd2 Nd7 20. Red1 { because of
Maroczy bind, d6 is more of a fixed target } { [%csl Bd6][%cal Yd1d6,Yf3g3,Yg3d6,Yg3g7] } 20... Ne5 21. Qg3 Be8 22. h3 b5 23. cxb5 axb5 24. Kh2 d5 25. f4 Ng6 26. e5 Ne7 27. h4 Qc3 28. Rd3 Qb2 29. h5 h6 30. R3d2 Qc3 31. Rd3 Qb2 32. Qh4 { stumble on this idea - just a tempo gainer on e7 but
also facilitates Rg3 } { [%csl Be7][%cal Yh4e7,Bh4f6,Bf6g7,Bd3g3,Bg3g7] } 32... Rd7 33. Rg3 Rc3 34. Bd3 { threat is Qf6 which causes
black a panic desperate move } { [%csl Bf6][%cal Bh4f6,Bf6g7] } 34... Rxd3 35. Rdxd3 Kf8 36. Qg4 g6 37. hxg6 Nxg6 38. f5 exf5 39. Qxf5 Qc1 40. Rxg6 { 1-0 Black resigns. } 1-0


