1. e4 c5 2. d4 cxd4 3. c3 d3 4. Bxd3 Nc6 5. Nf3 g6 6. h4 Nf6 7. e5 Ng4 8. Qe2 Bg7 9. h5 Ngxe5 10. Nxe5 Nxe5 11. Bc2 { an interesting pawn sac concept - and
Simon Williams himself likes harry the h pawn attacks } 11... d5 12. Bf4 Nc6 13. Na3 e5 14. O-O-O { technically here black is doing very well } 14... Qe7 (14... O-O $17) 15. Bg3 Be6 16. Qb5 f5 { controversial } (16... Rd8 17. Kb1 Rd7 $17) 17. f4 e4 (17... O-O-O 18. Bh4 Bf6 19. Bxf6 Qxf6 20. fxe5 Qxe5 21. Qc5 $17) 18. Bh4 Bf6 { mistake } (18... a6 19. Qb6 Qf7 20. Ba4) 19. Bxf6 Qxf6 20. Qxb7 Rc8 21. Ba4 { with the king still in the center there are lots of bouncy roads to King } 21... Bd7 22. Rxd5 O-O 23. hxg6 (23. Rxd7 Nd4 24. hxg6 Qxg6 25. Rhxh7 Ne2+ 26. Kb1 Rf7 27. Rdxf7) 23... Qxg6 24. Rxd7 Qxg2 25. Bb3+ { end of game } 25... Kh8 (25... Rf7 26. Qxc8+ Nd8 27. Qxd8+ Kg7 28. Rxf7+ Kg6 29. Qg8#) 26. Rdxh7# { 1-0 White wins by checkmate. } 1-0


