1. d4 b5 { [%cal Yb7b5] } 2. e4 Bb7 3. f3 a6 4. Be3 e6 5. Nd2 Nf6 6. c3 Be7 7. Bd3 { [%csl Yd3,Ye3,Bc3,Bd4,Be4,Bf3] } 7... d6 8. a4 c6 (8... b4 9. c4 O-O 10. Ne2 $16) 9. Ne2 Nbd7 10. O-O { fantasy position for white } 10... O-O 11. Ng3 Re8 12. axb5 axb5 13. Rxa8 Qxa8 14. Qc2 Bf8 15. b4 { discouraging c5 - prevention strategy } { [%cal Yc6c5,Yb4c5,Ye3c5] } 15... Qb8 (15... c5 16. bxc5 dxc5 17. Bxb5 Qc8 18. Qa2 $16) 16. Nb3 g6 17. Ra1 e5 18. Qf2 d5 { [%cal Yd6d5,Bd4e5,Be4d5] } 19. dxe5 Nxe5 20. Bc2 Bg7 (20... dxe4 21. Nxe4 Nxe4 22. Bxe4 c5 23. Bxb7 Qxb7 24. Nxc5 $16) (20... Nc4 21. Bd4 Nd7 22. exd5 cxd5 23. f4 Bg7 24. f5 Be5 25. Rf1 $16) 21. Ba7 Qc7 (21... Qa8 22. Bd4 Qb8 23. Nc5 $16) 22. Bb6 Qb8 23. Ba7 Qc7 24. Bb6 Qb8 25. Ba7 { Petrosian could have claimed draw here instead but believed in his position being advantageous if Spassky avoided 3-fold.Under these stakes Petrosian fundamentally beliueved in his c5 prevention strategy } 25... Qc8 { avoiding draw.But if game drawn Spassky would have to win last two games } { [%cal Bb8c8] } 26. Bd4 h5 (26... Qb8 27. Nc5 Nfd7 28. f4 Nxc5 29. bxc5 Nc4 30. Bxg7 Kxg7 31. e5 Qc7 32. Ne2 Qe7 33. Ra7 Kf8 34. Nd4 Ra8 35. Rxa8+ Bxa8 36. h4 Bb7 37. h5 Ke8 38. Qg3 Bc8 39. hxg6 hxg6 40. Bxg6 fxg6 41. Qxg6+ Kf8 42. Qxc6 Bd7 43. Qh6+ Qg7 44. Qxg7+ Kxg7 45. c6 Bc8 46. Kf2 Kf8 47. Nxb5 $16) 27. h3 (27. Nc5 h4 28. Nf1 h3 29. Ra7 dxe4 (29... Ba8 30. gxh3 $16) 30. fxe4 hxg2 31. Qxg2 Nh5 32. Kh1 Nd7 33. Nxb7 $16) (27. Bxe5 Rxe5 28. f4 Ng4 29. Qd2 Re8 30. h3 Nf6 (30... h4 31. Nf1 Nf6 32. e5 Nd7 33. Ne3 $16) 31. e5 Nd7 32. Qf2 $16) 27... h4 (27... dxe4 28. Nxe4 Nxe4 29. Bxe4 Qc7 30. Nc5 $16) 28. Nf1 dxe4 29. fxe4 Ned7 30. Nfd2 c5 { [%cal Yb7e4,Yf6e4] } 31. Nxc5 Nxc5 32. bxc5 { doubled pawns but option of Bxf6 is important.Pressure on f6 here.Checkmate ends the game and is often more important than pawn structure } (32. Bxc5 Bxe4 33. Bb3 Bd5 $10) 32... Bxe4 33. Bb3 { [%csl Bf7][%cal Yb3f7,Bf2f7] } (33. Bxf6 Bxc2 34. Bxg7 Kxg7 35. Nf3 $14) 33... Bf5 (33... Bd5 34. Bxf6 Bxf6 35. Bxd5 $16) (33... Qf5 34. Ra6 Nh5 35. Ra7 Rf8 36. Nxe4 Qxe4 37. Bxf7+ Kh8 38. Bxg7+ Nxg7 (38... Kxg7 39. Bd5+ Kh6 40. Qxf8+ $16) 39. Bxg6 Rxf2 40. Bxe4 $16) (33... Nh5 34. Bxf7+ Kh7 35. Bxe8 $16) 34. Ra7 Nd7 (34... Rf8 35. Qxh4 Qe8 36. Nf3 Qe4 37. Qxe4 Nxe4 38. c6 Nxc3 39. Bc5 (39. Bxc3 Bxc3 40. c7 Kg7 $10) 39... Rc8 40. Rxf7 Kh8 41. c7 $16) 35. Nf3 { end of game } 35... Bxd4 (35... Re7 36. Bxg7 Kxg7 37. Qd4+ f6 38. Qd6 Qxc5+ 39. Qxc5 Nxc5 40. Rxe7+ $16) (35... Rf8 36. Qxh4 { blacks missing h pawn is fatal } 36... Qe8 37. Ng5 Bxd4+ 38. cxd4 Kg7 39. Bxf7 Rxf7 40. Nxf7 Qxf7 41. c6 $18) 36. cxd4 { [%csl Bc5,Bd4][%cal Yc3d4] } 36... Qb8 37. Bxf7+ (37. Rxd7 Bxd7 38. Bxf7+ Kg7 39. Bxe8 Qxe8 40. d5) 37... Kxf7 (37... Kh8 38. Qxh4+ Kg7 39. Bxg6 Qxa7 40. Qh7+ Kf6 41. Qf7#) 38. Rxd7+ Bxd7 39. Ne5+ { [%cal Yf2f7,Ye5f7] } 39... Kg7 40. Qf7+ Kh6 41. Qxg6# { 1-0 White wins by checkmate. } 1-0


