1. d4 g6 2. e4 Bg7 3. Nf3 d6 4. Bc4 Nf6 5. Qe2 O-O 6. e5 Nfd7 { An opening
mistake - usually dxe5 is played here } (6... dxe5 7. dxe5 Nd5 $14) 7. h3 (7. e6 fxe6 (7... Nb6 8. exf7+ Kh8 9. h4 Nxc4 10. h5 g5 (10... Nb6 11. hxg6 h6 12. Ne5 dxe5 13. Rxh6+ Bxh6 14. Qxe5+ Bg7 15. Qh5+ Bh6 16. Qxh6#) 11. Bxg5 Nc6 12. Qxc4 $16) 8. Ng5 Nf6 9. Bxe6+ Kh8 10. Nf7+ Rxf7 11. Bxf7 $16) 7... Nb6 8. Bb3 Nc6 9. O-O dxe5 10. dxe5 Nd4 11. Nxd4 Qxd4 12. Re1 Bf5 13. c3 (13. Nd2 Qd7 14. a4 Rfd8 15. a5 Nd5 16. g4 Be6 17. Ne4 $16) 13... Qh4 (13... Qd3 14. e6 f6 $16) 14. Nd2 Rad8 { makes things worse for black } 15. Nf3 Qh5 16. Bf4 (16. g4 Qxh3 (16... Bxg4 17. hxg4 Qxg4+ 18. Kh1 h5 19. Rg1 Qh3+ 20. Nh2 $16) 17. gxf5 Qg4+ 18. Kh1 Qxf5 19. Qe4 $16) 16... Be6 17. Rad1 Bxb3 18. axb3 Qf5 19. Nd4 { [%cal Bf3d4,Bf5f4] } 19... Qxf4 { the
position seems entirely resignable } 20. e6 { [%cal Yf5f4,Ye6g8] } 20... Bxd4 21. cxd4 Rxd4 { [%cal Bd8d4] } 22. g3 Qd6 23. exf7+ Rxf7 24. Rxd4 Qxd4 25. Qe6 { a pin - does this mean our concentration
needs to be pinned because tactics flow from pins and it is as if the rook
really doesn't exist anymore while it is pinned. The power of the pinned piece
is illusionary. } { [%cal Ye6g8] } 25... Qxf2+ 26. Kh1 Qxg3 { From -10 to black to +1 for White in one
move because of a pinned rook! } { [%cal Bf2g3,Yf2f1] } 27. Rf1 { [%csl Bf7][%cal Yf1f7,Be6g8,Bg3h3,Be6h3] } 27... Kh8 (27... Kg7 28. Rxf7+ Kh6 29. Qxe7 Qxh3+ 30. Kg1 Qg3+ 31. Kh1 Qh3+ 32. Kg1 Qg3+ 33. Kf1 Qd3+ 34. Kf2 Qd2+ 35. Qe2 $16) 28. Rxf7 { [%cal Yf1f7,Be6h3] } 28... c6 29. Rxe7 { keeps hold of h3 pawn so easier to play than Qxe7 } (29. Qxe7 Qxh3+ 30. Kg1 Qg3+ 31. Kf1 Qh3+ 32. Ke2 Qg2+ 33. Kd1 Qd5+ 34. Kc1 Qxf7 35. Qxf7 h5 36. Qxb7 $16) 29... Nd5 { [%cal Ye6c8] } 30. Re8+ (30. Qc8#) (30. Qe5+ { [%cal Ye6e5,Ye5h8,Ye5g3] }) 30... Kg7 31. Qe5+ { [%cal Ye5g7,Ye5g3] } 31... Kh6 (31... Qxe5 32. Rxe5 Kf7 33. Kg2 $14 h6 34. Kf3 g5 $14) 32. Qxg3 { oops } { [%cal Ye5g3] } 1-0


