1. e4 e5 2. Nf3 Nc6 3. Bc4 Nf6 4. d3 Bc5 5. Be3 Bb6 6. Nc3 d6 7. h3 Ne7 8. Qd2 c6 9. Bb3 Ba5 10. Qe2 Ng6 11. Bd2 Qe7 12. g3 Be6 13. Nd1 Bb6 14. Ne3 Qd7 15. Bxe6 fxe6 16. h4 Bc7 17. h5 Nf8 18. Nh2 O-O-O 19. Nhg4 h6 20. Nxf6 gxf6 21. Qf3 Qg7 22. O-O-O Nd7 23. Ng2 Rh7 24. Nh4 Nf8 25. Kb1 Rd7 26. Bc1 c5 27. c4 Bd8 28. Qe2 Rf7 29. Ng2 f5 30. Rhg1 Nd7 (30... Qg4 31. Qxg4 (31. f3 Qxh5 $17) (31. Qd2 Qxh5 $17) 31... fxg4 32. Rdf1 $10) 31. Ne3 Qf8 32. Rdf1 Nb8 { white gets a nice knight on d5 now } (32... f4 33. Ng4 Bg5 $15) 33. exf5 exf5 34. Nd5 Nc6 35. Be3 (35. f4 Kb8 36. Bd2 Bf6 $16) 35... Kb8 36. f4 a6 37. g4 fxg4 38. Rxg4 Bg5 39. Rfg1 exf4 (39... Bxf4 40. Rg8 $18) 40. Bxf4 Ka7 (40... Nd4 41. Qe4 Rf5 $10) 41. Qe4 Ne5 (41... Rhg7 $10 42. a3 (42. Bxg5 Rxg5 43. Rxg5 Rf1+ 44. Kc2 Nd4+ 45. Kc3 hxg5 46. Rxf1 Qxf1 47. Kd2 Qf2+ 48. Kd1 Nf3 49. Qe3 Qf1+ 50. Kc2 Nd4+ 51. Kd2 Qg2+ 52. Kd1 g4 53. Nc3 Qc2+ 54. Ke1 Qh2 55. Kd1 g3 $17) 42... Bxf4 43. Rxg7 Rxg7 44. Rxg7 Qxg7 45. Qxf4 Ne5 $10) 42. Bxe5 Rf1+ { mistake because h7 is hanging } (42... dxe5 43. a3 (43. Qxe5 Rf1+ 44. Kc2 (44. Rxf1 Qxf1+ 45. Kc2 Qc1+ 46. Kb3 Qd1+ 47. Ka3 Qxg4 $17) 44... Rxg1 45. Rxg1 Qf2+ 46. Kb3 Qxg1 $17) 43... Rf1+ 44. Rxf1 Qxf1+ 45. Ka2 $16) 43. Rxf1 Qxf1+ 44. Kc2 Qc1+ 45. Kb3 Qd1+ (45... dxe5 46. Rxg5 (46. Qxh7 Qd1+ 47. Ka3 Qxg4 $14) 46... Qxg5 47. Qxh7 Qxh5 48. Ka3 $16) 46. Ka3 Rd7 { no game was ever won by resigning } 47. Nc3 (47. Rxg5 hxg5 48. Qf5 Rd8 49. Qg6 dxe5 50. Qb6+ Kb8 51. Qxd8+ $16) 47... Qc2 48. Rg2 Qc1 49. Bh8 Rd8 50. Bg7 Rd7 51. Bh8 Rd8 52. Bg7 Rd7 53. Qg6 Bd2 54. Qg4 Bxc3 55. Bxc3 Rc7 56. Qe4 b5 57. Be1 Qd1 { like Fischer, aiming for killer common squares like Qa4 mate } { [%csl Ba4][%cal Yd1a4] } 58. cxb5 axb5 59. b4 Qc1+ 60. Rb2 Kb6 61. bxc5+ dxc5 (61... Rxc5 62. Qb4 $16) 62. Qe6+ Rc6 63. Qe2 Rc7 64. Bf2 { oopsie - this allows a mate in 2 - weakness of last move disaster - another way of saying this neglecting a key square - letting the opponent in on a key square etc } { [%csl Gc3][%cal Be1f2,Be1a5] } (64. Bd2 b4+ 65. Kb3 Qh1 66. Kc2 $16) 64... Qc3+ 65. Rb3 Ra7# { 0-1 Black wins by checkmate. } { [%cal Ya7a3,Bc3a1,Bc3b2] } 0-1


