1. e4 d6 2. d4 Nf6 3. Nc3 g6 4. f4 { The Austrian Attack } 4... Bg7 5. Nf3 O-O 6. e5 dxe5 7. fxe5 Nd5 8. Bc4 Nb6 9. Bb3 c5 10. O-O cxd4 11. Ne4 Nc6 12. Qe1 { At the cost of a pawn, this seems like a remarkably "easy to play" plan for White essentially involving Qh4, then Bh6, then N(any)-g5 then take on g7 and then Qxh7 mate. So much for the Hypermodern theory of undermining White's center. Unless Black plays with extreme accuracy, King safety is likely to become the dominating factor here in White's favour. } { [%csl Bh7][%cal Ye1h4,Bc1h6,Yf3g5,Ye4g5,Bh6g7,Bh4h7,Bg5h7] } 12... Bf5 (12... Nxe5 13. Nxe5 Bxe5 14. Bh6 { The issue here is the f7 soft spot } { [%csl Rf7][%cal Gb3f7,Gf1f7] } 14... Re8 15. Bxf7+ Kh8 16. Bxe8 $16) 13. Qh4 Bxe4 (13... Rc8 { I give Rc8 as an example of a disastrously "slow" move here. White is planning Bh6 and N(any)-g5 with a mating effect on h7 } 14. Bh6 Bxe4 15. Ng5 { No need to recapture - "checkmate ends the game" - h7 is a "killer common square" to celebrate here. Black's defensive guards seem to be on the Q-side } 15... Bd5 16. Bxg7 Kxg7 17. Qxh7#) (13... Nxe5 14. Nxe5 Bxe5 15. Rxf5 gxf5 16. Ng5 h5 17. Qxh5 Bxh2+ 18. Kh1 Kg7 19. Qh7+ Kf6 20. Qh6+ Ke5 21. Nxf7+ Rxf7 (21... Ke4 22. Qe6+ Be5 23. Qxe5#) 22. Qe6#) 14. Qxe4 e6 { black is technically better here } 15. Bg5 Qc7 16. Rae1 h6 17. Bf6 Bxf6 (17... a5 { with plan of a4 and ra5 would help undermine
e5 pawn } 18. c3 dxc3 19. bxc3 a4 20. Bxe6 (20. Bc2 Ra5 21. Bxg7 Kxg7 22. h4 Nd7 23. h5 Ndxe5 24. hxg6 Nxg6 $17) 20... fxe6 21. Qxg6 Qf7 $17) 18. exf6 { the
dreaded thorn pawn - a goal hanging pawn - would not be allowed in Euroopean
football :) } { [%csl Gf6][%cal Bf6g7] } 18... Nd7 19. Bxe6 { threat is now Qxg6 check } { [%csl Bg6,Bf7][%cal Ye4g6] } 19... Kh7 (19... fxe6 20. Qxg6+ Kh8 21. Qg7# { the power of the thorn pawn - behold! }) 20. Qh4 { threat is now
ng5+ } 20... Nxf6 21. Bxf7 Kg7 (21... Qxf7 22. Ng5+ Kg7 23. Nxf7 $16) (21... Rxf7 22. Ng5+ Kg8 23. Nxf7 Qxf7 24. Rxf6 $16) 22. Nxd4 Qxf7 23. Ne6+ Kg8 24. Nxf8 Rxf8 25. Qxh6 Qg7 26. Qxg7+ Kxg7 27. Re6 Rf7 28. c3 Nd8 29. Re2 Nc6 30. Ref2 { white is better here overall } 30... g5 31. h3 Ne5 { makes things worse for black } 32. Rf5 Ned7 33. Rxg5+ Kh6 34. Rgf5 Kg6 35. g4 Re7 36. Kg2 Nd5 37. Rxd5 { and with
this win a new lichess bullet record set of 3379 - Annotations by Kingscrusher
:) } 1-0


