1. d4 d5 2. Bf4 (2. Nf3 { downside -d1 ht diagonal - does make it also downside ready for lenningrad dutch and also kings indian style systems.If black later kicks the bishop, light squares weakened }) 2... c5 3. e3 { Keeping d1-h5 diagonal free } 3... Nc6 4. c3 Qb6 5. Qb3 Nf6 (5... Qxb3 6. axb3 cxd4 7. exd4 Bf5 8. b4 $16) 6. Nd2 { again keeping d1-h5 clear } 6... c4 7. Qc2 Nh5 { on a light square - and now perk of keeping diagnal clear is made use of.The knight can be counter attacked } (7... Bf5 8. Qxf5 Qxb2 9. Qb1 Qxc3 10. Nf3 $16) 8. Bg5 h6 { weakening light squares } 9. Bh4 g5 10. Be2 { the facility which has made made available from the start is now used } 10... Ng7 (10... gxh4 11. Bxh5 e5 12. Ndf3 e4 13. Nxh4 $16) 11. Bg3 { the painful london system bishop has not been swapped off } 11... Bf5 { black has temporary grip on e4, but white has great undermining opportunities } 12. Qc1 e6 13. Ngf3 Qa5 (13... Be7 { would make e4 less powerful than Qa5 }) (13... Nh5 14. Be5 f6 15. Nh4 gxh4 (15... fxe5 16. Bxh5+ $16) (15... Ng7 16. Nxf5 fxe5 17. Nxg7+ Bxg7 18. Bh5+ Kd8 19. b3 $16) 16. Bxh5+ Ke7 17. Bf4) 14. e4 { totally thematic move } 14... Bh7 { White has the ability to mine pawn structure sometimes at d5 } (14... dxe4 15. Nxc4 Qd8 16. Nfe5 $16) 15. O-O Be7 16. Re1 O-O 17. Ne5 Nxe5 18. Bxe5 f6 { weakening more light squares } 19. Bg3 Rfe8 20. h4 b5 21. b4 Qd8 (21... cxb3 22. axb3 Qb6 23. exd5 exd5 24. hxg5 hxg5 25. Bf3 $16) 22. a4 a5 (22... a6 23. Bf3 Bg6 24. exd5 exd5 25. Nf1 Bf7 26. Ne3 $16) 23. axb5 axb4 24. Rxa8 Qxa8 25. exd5 exd5 26. Bf3 { threatening nxc4 } 26... Qd8 { Queen is struggling to hold on to d5.White has raking bishops. } 27. hxg5 hxg5 28. b6 bxc3 29. Qxc3 Qxb6 30. Bxd5+ Kf8 31. Nxc4 Qb5 32. Ne3 Rd8 33. Qc7 Qd7 34. Qa5 Nh5 35. Bc7 Rc8 36. Bh2 Nf4 (36... Rd8 37. Bf3 Ng7 38. Nd5 $16 Bd6 39. Nxf6 Bxh2+ 40. Kh1 Qxd4 41. Nxh7+ Kg8 42. Nxg5 $16) 37. Bxf4 gxf4 38. Nc4 Qf5 39. Qa7 Qxd5 (39... Bb4 40. Qf7#) 40. Qxe7+ Kg8 41. Nb6 { game ended here } 41... Qf5 42. Nxc8 Qxc8 43. Qxf6 $16 { I commented about hnow London system players worldwide might want to recheck their Nf3 preference - trivia and downsides explored dramatically. } 1-0


