1. d4 { Montreal (1979).Montreal (/?m?ntri'??l/ (About this soundlisten) MUN-tree-AWL; officially Montréal, French: [m?~?eal] (About this soundlisten)) is the most populous city in the Canadian province of Quebec and the second-most populous city in Canada.In the spring of 1979, Lubomir Kavalek, along with Czech filmmakers Milos Forman and Ivan Passer, organized a double round robin tournament to be held in Montreal, Quebec from April 10th to May 7th.Dubbed "The Tournament of Stars", the event was attended by ten of the very strongest grandmasters at the time, including the world champion Karpov } 1... Nf6 2. c4 e6 3. Nf3 b6 4. e3 Bb7 5. Bd3 d5 6. b3 Bd6 7. O-O O-O 8. Bb2 Nbd7 9. Nbd2 Qe7 10. Rc1 Rad8 11. Qc2 c5 12. cxd5 exd5 13. dxc5 bxc5 14. Qc3 Rfe8 15. Rfd1 d4 16. exd4 cxd4 17. Qa5 { mistake } (17. Nxd4 Bf4 (17... Bxh2+ 18. Kxh2 Ng4+ 19. Kg3 (19. Kg1 Qh4 20. N2f3 (20. Bxh7+ Kh8 (20... Kxh7 21. Qh3 Qxh3 22. gxh3 Nge5 23. Re1 Nd3 24. Rxe8 Rxe8 25. Rc7 Re1+ 26. Nf1 Nxb2 27. Rxb7 $16) 21. Qh3 Qxf2+ 22. Kh1 Bxg2+ 23. Qxg2 Qxg2+ 24. Kxg2 Ne3+ 25. Kg3 Nxd1 26. Rxd1 Kxh7 27. Nc6 Rc8 28. Nc4 Rc7 29. Nb4 Nf8 30. Rd5 $16) (20. N4f3 Qxf2+ 21. Kh1 Nde5 22. Bxh7+ Kxh7 23. Rf1 Qb6 24. Ng5+ Kg8 25. Qh3 Qg6 $17) 20... Qxf2+ 21. Kh1 Nde5 (21... Re5 22. Bf5 Rc5 23. Bxg4 Rxc3 24. Bxc3 $16) 22. Rd2 Qg3 23. Rf1 Qf4 $15) 19... Qd6+ (19... Qe5+ 20. f4 Qe3+ 21. N2f3 Qf2+ 22. Kh3 Ndf6 23. Rf1 Qe3 24. g3 $16) 20. f4 Ndf6 (20... Re3+ 21. N2f3 Ndf6 22. Qc7 $18) 21. Qc5 Qb8 22. Qc7 Qa8 23. Bb5 $16) 18. g3 (18. a3 { token move to see what the threats are } 18... Ne5 19. b4 (19. N2f3 Bxf3 20. Nxf3 Nxf3+ 21. gxf3 Nh5 22. h3 Qg5+ 23. Kf1 Be5 24. h4 Qf4 25. Qc2 Bxb2 26. Qxb2 Qh2 $17) 19... Nxd3 20. Qxd3 Ng4 21. h3 Qh4 22. Rf1 Bh2+ 23. Kh1 Nxf2+ 24. Rxf2 Qxf2 $17) (18. Nf5 Qe6 19. Qc4 (19. Qb4 Ne5 20. Nxg7 Kxg7 21. Qxf4 Rxd3 22. Re1 Nfd7 23. Rc7 Qh6 24. Qxh6+ Kxh6 25. Bc1 Rb8 26. Nf3+ Kg6 27. Nh4+ Kh5 28. Nf5 Kg6 29. Nh4+ Kh5 30. Nf5) (19. a3 Ne5 20. Bb1 Qd5 21. Qh3 Bxd2 22. Rc2 Neg4 23. Rcxd2 Qxd2 24. Rxd2 Re1#) 19... Nc5 $10) 18... Be5 19. Bf1 Ng4 20. Nc4 (20. N2f3 Qf6 21. Bg2 Nf8 22. Rd2 Rc8 23. Qb4 Rxc1+ 24. Bxc1 Bxd4 25. Qxb7 $10) 20... Qf6 21. Rc2 Nxh2 22. Bg2 (22. Kxh2 Qh6+ 23. Bh3 (23. Kg1 Qh1#) 23... Nf6 24. f3 Bc8 25. Nxe5 Qxh3+ 26. Kg1 Rxe5 27. Rg2 Rh5 $17) 22... Bxd4 23. Rxd4 Nf3+ 24. Bxf3 Bxf3 25. Rf4 Qxc3 26. Bxc3 Ba8 $10) (17. Qxd4 Nc5 18. Qc3 Nxd3 19. Qxd3 Bxh2+ 20. Nxh2 Rxd3 $17) (17. Qc2 Ne5 18. Nxe5 (18. Re1 Bxf3 19. Nxf3 Nxf3+ 20. gxf3 Qxe1+ 21. Rxe1 Rxe1+ 22. Kg2 Nh5 23. f4 Nxf4+ 24. Kf3 Nxd3 25. Qxd3 Be7 $17) 18... Qxe5 19. Nf3 Bxf3 20. gxf3 Qxh2+ 21. Kf1 Qh1#) 17... Ne5 18. Nxe5 Bxe5 19. Nc4 { makes things much worse } (19. Ba3 Qe6 20. Re1 Qg4 21. f3 Bxh2+ 22. Kxh2 Qh4+ 23. Kg1 Rxe1+ 24. Nf1 Rde8 $17) (19. Qc5 Qe6 20. Qc4 Qg4 21. g3 Bf4 $17) (19. Qxa7 Ng4 20. Nf3 Ra8 21. Qc5 Qf6 22. Bxd4 Bxf3 23. gxf3 Bxd4 24. Qxd4 Qxd4 25. Bxh7+ Kxh7 26. Rxd4 Ne5 $17) 19... Rd5 (19... Bxh2+ 20. Kxh2 Ng4+ 21. Kg3 (21. Kh3 Nxf2+ 22. Kg3 Nxd1 23. Rxd1 Rd5 24. Qd2 Rg5+ 25. Kh2 Rh5+ 26. Kg1 Qh4 $17) 21... Rd5 22. Qe1 Ne3 23. Nxe3 Qd6+ 24. Kf3 Rg5+ 25. Ke2 Rxe3+ 26. fxe3 Rxg2+ 27. Qf2 Rxf2+ 28. Kxf2 Qh2+ 29. Ke1 dxe3 30. Rc2 Qh4+ 31. Kf1 Qf4+ 32. Ke1 Qg3+ 33. Kf1 h5 $17) 20. Qd2 (20. Qxa7 Bxh2+ 21. Kxh2 Ng4+ 22. Kg1 Qh4 23. Ne5 Qxf2+ 24. Kh1 Rdxe5 25. Qxb7 Rh5#) 20... Bxh2+ 21. Kxh2 (21. Kf1 Rh5 22. Re1 Bf4 23. Rxe7 Rxe7 24. Kg1 Bxd2 25. Nxd2 Nd5 26. Bxd4 Nf4 27. Bf1 Rg5 28. Bxa7 Rxg2+ 29. Bxg2 Ne2+ 30. Kh2 Nxc1 $17) (21. Kh1 Rh5 22. Ba3 Bd6+ 23. Kg1 Ng4 24. Bxd6 Qh4 25. Bxh7+ Kh8 26. Bh2 Qxh2+ 27. Kf1 Qxg2#) 21... Rh5+ 22. Kg1 (22. Kg3 Ne4+ 23. Bxe4 Qh4+ 24. Kf3 Qxe4+ 25. Kg3 Qh4#) 22... Ng4 { game ended here } 23. Re1 (23. f3 Rh1+ 24. Kxh1 Qh4+ 25. Kg1 Qh2+ 26. Kf1 Qh1#) (23. Qf4 Qh4 24. Bxh7+ Kh8 25. Qh2 Qxh2+ 26. Kf1 Qxg2#) 23... Rh1+ 24. Kxh1 Qh4+ 25. Kg1 Qh2+ 26. Kf1 Qxg2# { This game received the second brilliancy prize at Montreal 1979.Interestingly, Tal did not agree.He considered it a pretty obvious sacrifice.HIS picks for the best game were Karpovs win(with Black) against Timman and his own game against Huebner.Tal finished with 12/18 same score as Karpov join first.It was only by a brilliant win against Ljubojevic with the black pieces in the penultimate round that Karpov was able to tie Tal in the final round and share first place with him. } 0-1


