1. f4 { Video here: https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=1z8yR2xveJw } (1. d4 Nf6 2. c4) 1... Nh6 { A03 Bird Opening: Horsefly Defense } 2. f5? { 5 Odds game - game
starts at Move } 2... Nxf5 3. Nf3 Nh6? 4. Ng1? Ng8? 5. e4 { GAME STARTS HERE
after Odds prelude..... of pawn given up } 5... e6?? { STOCKFISH TAKES FRENCH
DEFENCE STRUCTURE AT ITS PERIL !!!! It seems both Ethereal and Houdini chose
e5 here and both win with Black against leela. Therefore also both of those
engines manage to get e5 and Bc5 in, to stop White castling and show all
downsides of missing f pawn. Stockfish on the other hand with e6 manages to
show up all the upsides of the missing f pawn by playing instead e6 which
allows White d4 and the diagonal a7-g1 not such an issue at all.  It seems
after depth 31 on one my machines, goes to e6 assuming Nf3 from White and then
