1. e4 Nc6 { The Nimzovich defence or sometimes called the Queen Knights Tango } 2. Nf3 { d6 is the most popular move here according to the Lichess masters opening book. e5 is the 2nd most popular. } 2... d6!? 3. d4 Nf6 (3... Bg4 4. Bb5 a6 5. Bxc6+ bxc6 6. h3 Bh5 7. Nc3 e6 8. Qd3 Nf6 9. Bg5 Be7 10. g4 Bg6 11. O-O-O O-O $14) 4. Nc3 Bg4 5. Be3 e6 6. h3 Bh5 { Short vs Leko ended in a draw from this position } 7. Be2 (7. d5 exd5 8. exd5 Bxf3 9. Qxf3 Ne5 10. Qe2 a6 11. f4 Ned7 12. g4 Qe7 13. O-O-O O-O-O $14) 7... Be7 8. O-O O-O 9. a4 Bg6 $10 *


